{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Service Boundary & Audit Enforcer",
  "description": "When a service file is saved, verify it owns business logic correctly: every state-changing write also writes an audit log, multi-step operations run inside a transaction, all DB access goes through a repository (no direct Drizzle in services), all third-party calls go through integrations/* (no direct AWS/OpenAI/MSG91 SDKs), and tenant context is read from cls/context (never from request bodies).",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "**/server/src/modules/**/*.service.ts",
      "**/server/src/modules/**/services/**/*.ts"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A NestJS service was just saved. Audit it against the RADHA service-layer contract. Read-only review.\n\nHard rules (each violation = High):\n1. No direct DB access: services must NOT import drizzle-orm operators or `db` client directly. All queries go through a repository class injected via DI. Flag any `db.select`, `db.insert`, `db.update`, `db.delete`, raw SQL, or `drizzle-orm` operator imports in this file.\n2. No direct third-party SDKs: services must NOT import `@aws-sdk/*`, `openai`, `firebase-admin`, MSG91 clients, `@google-cloud/vision`, `@sentry/node`, etc. Those calls live in `server/src/integrations/<provider>/`. The service injects the integration wrapper.\n3. Audit log on writes: every method that performs a create/update/delete/state-transition also calls AuditLogService.write (or equivalent). The audit entry must include actor user id, tenant id, entity type+id, action, before/after diff (or `null` for create/delete). Flag write methods missing audit calls.\n4. Transactions: any method that does >1 write OR a write-then-read sequence must run inside `db.transaction()` (passed through repository) or accept a transaction context. Flag interleaved awaits over multiple writes outside a transaction.\n5. Tenant context: tenant_id and store_id come from the cls request context or an injected ContextService — never from a request body. Flag any code that reads `dto.tenantId` or similar.\n6. Error handling: throw typed domain errors from common/errors, never raw `Error` or `HttpException` for business cases that have a typed equivalent.\n7. Idempotency: methods exposed to retry-prone callers (BullMQ consumers, webhook handlers, OTP) must check or write idempotency_records.\n8. PII in logs: no logger.log of phone, email, OTP, token, full address, or full name. Use redacted ids.\n9. Single responsibility: flag service methods longer than ~80 lines or doing more than one logical step (extract sub-services).\n\nOutput:\n- Group findings by severity. Each entry: method name + line, rule broken, one-line fix (or short snippet).\n- One-line summary: \"Service contract: PASS\" or \"Service contract: FAIL — N High issues\".\n- If clean, say so. Do not invent issues."
  }
}